> > Ok, I think this fixes it without extraneously incrementing the taffy ids.
> 
> @StrikeForceZero Hmm... this seems to be creating one "implicit viewport node" per camera (viewport) rather than one for each direct child of the camera (viewport). I think this will break the case when there are multiple ui trees as children of a camera which are currently laid out independently (but I think the proposed patch will cause them to be laid out in a grid).

Unless I'm not understanding, it appears to have no visible effect on the root child nodes. 

Below is an example of two text nodes height and width set to 100%, taking up the entire viewport.

![image](https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/assets/983413/27500bb2-7925-4f33-8e96-4b8a0f90932b)

```rust
    commands.spawn((
            TextBundle {
                text: Text::from_section("hello world static", TextStyle { ..default() }),
                style: Style {
                    width: Val::Percent(100.),
                    height: Val::Percent(100.),
                    ..default()
                },
                background_color: Color::srgb(1., 0., 0.).into(),
                ..default()
            },
            TargetCamera(left_camera_entity),
        ));

    commands.spawn((
        TextBundle {
            text: Text::from_section("hello world static", TextStyle { ..default() }),
            style: Style {
                width: Val::Percent(100.),
                height: Val::Percent(100.),
                ..default()
            },
            background_color: Color::srgb(0., 0., 1.).into(),
            ..default()
        },
        TargetCamera(right_camera_entity),
    ));
```
    
and here's one with children on one side
    
    
![image](https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/assets/983413/36c91742-4576-4402-9c98-5f7f5d03cce1)


```rust
    commands.spawn((
            TextBundle {
                text: Text::from_section("hello world static", TextStyle { ..default() }),
                style: Style {
                    display: Display::Flex,
                    width: Val::Percent(100.),
                    height: Val::Percent(100.),
                    ..default()
                },
                background_color: Color::srgb(1., 0., 0.).into(),
                ..default()
            },
            TargetCamera(left_camera_entity),
        ));

    commands.spawn((
        NodeBundle {
            style: Style {
                display: Display::Flex,
                flex_direction: FlexDirection::Column,
                width: Val::Percent(100.),
                height: Val::Percent(100.),
                ..default()
            },
            background_color: Color::srgb(0.5, 0.5, 0.5).into(),
            ..default()
        },
        TargetCamera(right_camera_entity),
    )).with_children(|children| {
        children.spawn((
            TextBundle {
                text: Text::from_section("b", TextStyle { ..default() }),
                style: Style {
                    display: Display::Flex,
                    height: Val::Percent(50.),
                    ..default()
                },
                background_color: Color::srgb(0., 0., 1.).into(),
                ..default()
            },
        ));
        children.spawn((
            TextBundle {
                text: Text::from_section("a", TextStyle { ..default() }),
                style: Style {
                    display: Display::Flex,
                    height: Val::Percent(50.),
                    ..default()
                },
                background_color: Color::srgb(0., 1., 0.).into(),
                ..default()
            },
        ));
    });
```
